c Policy" width="100%" height="auto" ></div><h1 class="page-intro-title-text h2 hyundai-motor-korea-foundation-center-for-korean-history-and-public-policy">Hyundai Motor-Korea Foundation Center for Korean History and Public Policy</h1></div><div class="page-intro-text wysiwyg-content"><p>The Center for Korean History and Public Policy was established in 2015 with the generous support of the Hyundai Motor Company and the Korea Foundation to provide a coherent, long-term platform for improving historical understanding of Korea and informing the public policy debate on the Korean peninsula in the United States and beyond.</p></div><div class="page-intro-supplemental"><div class="page-intro-supplemental-column"><h6 class="page-intro-supplemental-title h6">Connect With Us</h6><ul class="page-intro-social"><li class="page-intro-social-item"><a href="https://twitter.com/Korea_Center" class="icon-twitter"><span class="sr-text">Twitter</span></a></li><li class="page-intro-social-item"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/wilsoncenterkorea/" class="icon-instagram"><span class="sr-text">Instagram</span></a></li><li class="page-intro-social-item"><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/160615739@N02" class="icon-flickr"><span class="sr-text">Flickr</span></a></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class="insights-block"><div class="insights-block-inner"><h3 class="insights-block-title h3">Recent Insights</h3><div class="insights-block-content"><a class="insights-block-featured-image" href="/blog-post/south-koreas-2024-national-assembly-elections-what-comes-next" data-type="blog-post"><picture><source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/insights/public/media/uploads/images/Shutterstock_1698329482.webp" type="image/webp"/><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/insights/public/media/uploads/images/Shutterstock_1698329482.jpg" width="749" height="615" alt="2024 Korean Elections Banners" loading="lazy"></picture></a><div class="insights-block-featured-teaser"><a class="teaser" data